      "writtenOn": "2017-09-28T21:26:32Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "I don\u0027t think this is right. Here\u0027s terminfo for vt100:\n\n    csr\u003d\\E[%i%p1%d;%p2%dr\n\nfor screen:\n\n    csr\u003d\\E[%i%p1%d;%p2%dr\n\nfor tmux:\n\n    csr\u003d\\E[%i%p1%d;%p2%dr\n\nI collected these from a few running systems with:\n\n    infocmp $TERM\n\nThese are defined in the upstream terminfo file which is a decades old effort to collect all of these quirks empirically: http://invisible-island.net/ncurses/terminfo.ti.html .\n\nThese escape codes are defined in: https://linux.die.net/man/5/termcap",
      "range": {
        "startLine": 169,
        "startChar": 0,
        "endLine": 169,
        "endChar": 51
      },
      "revId": "593e83ad4bd1b13b72f470e0cc342d305bcef4d1",
