      "writtenOn": "2017-09-28T23:15:23Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "i could be misunderstanding this, but isn\u0027t that the same as what i\u0027m sending? i had trouble finding a good source for this, but per the o\u0027reilly \"termcap \u0026 terminfo\" book (https://books.google.com/books?id\u003dGsUMLqtYI1UC\u0026printsec\u003dfrontcover\u0026dq\u003dtermcap\u0026hl\u003den\u0026sa\u003dX\u0026ved\u003d0ahUKEwjE6MKN_8jWAhWIsFQKHeLeC00Q6AEIKTAA#v\u003donepage\u0026q\u003dtermcap\u0026f\u003dfalse):\n\n%i means 1-based values\n%p1 and %p2 push the first and second parameters onto the stack\n%d means decimal number\n\nso doesn\u0027t this boil down to \\033[\u003cstart\u003e;\u003cend\u003er ?",
      "parentUuid": "2951e408_765e5da2",
